{"id":"1402.6679","submitter":"Kunihiko Uehara","authors":"Minoru Fujimoto and Kunihiko Uehara","title":"The algorithm for the $2d$ different primes and Hardy-Littlewood\n  conjecture","comments":"8 Pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.NT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We give an estimation of the existence density for the $2d$ different primes\nby using a new and simple algorithm for getting the $2d$ different primes. The\nalgorithm is a kind of the sieve method, but the remainders are the central\nnumbers between the $2d$ different primes. We may conclude that there exist\ninfinitely many $2d$ different primes including the twin primes in case of\n$d=1$ because we can give the lower bounds of the existence density for the\n$2d$ different primes in this algorithm. We also discuss the Hardy-Littlewood\nconjecture and the Sophie Germain primes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 25 Jan 2014 10:29:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-02-27"}
